attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any method designed to collect (and later examine) live larvae from a field population. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any method designed to collect (and later examine) eggs from a field population. [PT:PT]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any eggs collection method which targets naturally deposited eggs. [PT:PT]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any eggs collection method that uses scraping. [PT:PT]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any method designed to collect (and later examine) live pupae from a field population. [PT:PT]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any catch of live specimens method meant to collect mosquitoes from aquatic environment. [PT:PT]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any method designed to collect (and later examine) live adults from a field population. [PT:PT]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any population catch method meant to collect dead specimens. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Any method designed to identify the species of the insect specimen under study, usually caught /isolated from a field population. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Genetic crossings between specimens collected in the field to determine whether fertile progeny is produced. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Analysis of polytene chromosomes to determine, through cytological examination of the banding pattern, the species that they belong to. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Electrophoresis to determine the isozymes that are present in a given mosquito/population, from which in some cases the species can be determined. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Examination of the morphology to determine, through the use of specific \taxonomical keys\ the species a specimen belongs to. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Use of a variety of PCR-based procedures to determine the species that a specimen belongs to. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Usage of labeled DNA fragments of variable length (usually 100-1000 bases long), to detect in DNA or RNA samples the presence of nucleotide sequences that are complementary to the sequence in the probe through hybridization. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: A series of analytical procedures to detect the presence, and estimate the frequency of resistance phenotypes, or resistance-associated markers in wild populations at a given time or over a defined time period. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: An assay used to determine enzyme activity associated with insecticide resistance phenotypes. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: An assay used to determine changes at genomic DNA or mRNA levels associated with insecticide resistance phenotypes. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: In vivo assays to measure the rate of insecticide uptake, translocation or excretion by a living organism. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Bioassay is a shorthand commonly used term for biological assay and is a type of scientific experiment. Bioassays are typically conducted to measure the effects of a substance on a living organism. [Wikipedia:bioassay]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Antibody-based assays to measure, in a biological sample, levels of antigens. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Bioassay at preset insecticide dosage scoring mortality to determine resistance of a population. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Diagnostic assay, performed in a glass bottle coated with insecticides. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Diagnostic assay, using WHO cone kit. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Diagnostic assay, using WHO paper kit. [KL:KL]

attribute.name: definition
attribute.value: Diagnostic assay, testing survival of larvae in a medium supplemented with insecticide. [KL:KL]
